 If we are careful to count how many times it has spun around, 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{n}$
\end_inset

 can be any real number.
 The circle map just models this situation as 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{n+1}=q_{n}+\omega-K\sin2\pi q_{n}$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 some number that captures the combination of teh spring constant and the
 moment of inertia of the free disk.
 There are electrical models of this system as well.
 The weak coupling can be thought of as an antenna, picking up a signal
 from a distant but fixed station broadcasting a pure carrier with frequency
 
